It's all about Volume and the Flow of Money

From the Bearbullwaves.com web site
http://bearbullwaves.com/OnBalanceVolumeTheBasic.aspx

"...There are many indicators available to measure volume and the flow of money
for a particular stock, index or security. One of the most popular volume
indicators over the years has been the Accumulation/Distribution Line. The
basic premise behind volume indicators, including the Accumulation/Distribution
Line, is that <u>volume precedes price</u>. Volume reflects the amount of
shares traded in a particular stock, and is a direct reflection of the money
flowing into and out of a stock. <u>Many times before a stock advances, there
will be period of increased volume just prior to the move.</u> Most volume or
money flow indicators are designed to identify early increases in positive or
negative volume flow to gain an edge before the price moves. (Note: the terms
"money flow" and "volume flow" are essentially interchangeable.)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

I think this heavy volume reflects the beginning of a "new" significant bull
move in these stocks.

I will be looking to add to my positions on any sell offs.

