Date:3/10/2011 9:58:14 AM
From:ValueGuy
I took a look at AGNC too. Seems to be good value at first glance but this is
true for all the other REITs as well (take a look at NLY for example).

From what I understand, these REITs invests in Agency MBSs, so with the low
interest rate environment that has been prevalent for the past couple of years,
they have minted! AGNC is relatively new when compared to NLY, but I think they
have the highest divi yield around for now. In terms of a divi play they're
good as they pay quarterly divis (though some REITs like ARR pay monthly
divis).

Following on from the point I made about the low interest rate environment...it
stands to reason that if interest rates increase, then these REITs would start
to feel the pain. Therefore you will probably see a decrease in the divis that
they pay out, though that is just my opinion as I have not really done any
meaningful analysis.

Many pundits are predicting that interest rates are going to increase after QE2
ends in June, and that will probably be bad for MBSs.
