%BOM---------------------
Date:3/11/2011 12:33:26 AM
From:Elroy
Can anyone explain to me how they manage to pay 18.6% dividend?

AGNC is basically just a pool of capital used to speculate on interest rates.
The fund manager borrow short term (~1 month, paying maybe 0.6% annual
interest) and invest the money in longer term notesw (perhaps 2 years, earning
2.8% annually). The pocket the differential (2.2%). They then leverage that
position up 7x or 8x. As long as their is a big gap between short term and
longer term rates, they'll be fine. If rates change in a way that they don't
anticipate, then they may run into trouble.

So it's not really a business, just a highly levered pool of money.
